## 3. Notification permission (PushInviteStage + native skip)

We must always know: **granted / denied / skipped / os_denied / snoozed.**

In `lib/veil/push_invite_stage.dart` use the **real** result of the OS
dialog (`askPermission()` returns the bool — do not re-read the vault):

```dart
Future<void> _accept(BuildContext context) async {
  Insight.event('push_invite_accept');
  final bool granted = await pushHub.askPermission();
  Insight.tag('notif_permission', granted ? 'granted' : 'denied');
  Insight.event(granted ? 'push_granted' : 'push_denied');
  if (!granted) await vault.writeInviteCooldown(_cooldownTarget());
  if (context.mounted) _forward(context);
}

Future<void> _skip(BuildContext context) async {
  Insight.event('push_invite_skip');
  Insight.tag('notif_permission', 'skipped');
  await vault.writeInviteCooldown(_cooldownTarget());
  if (context.mounted) _forward(context);
}
```

Also emit `Insight.screen('push_invite');` when the screen is shown (add a
one-shot in `build` guarded by a bool, or convert to `StatefulWidget` and
call it in `initState`).

In `FlowRouter._toWeb`, the **else** branch skips the invite for returning
users — classify those sessions too so the tag is never blank:

```dart
} else {
  Insight.tag('notif_permission',
      widget.vault.isPushAllowed()
          ? 'granted'
          : widget.vault.isPushBlockedByOs()
              ? 'os_denied'
              : 'snoozed');
  Navigator.of(context).pushReplacement(/* WebStage */);
}
```

