## 5. Remaining screens

- `lib/veil/offline_stage.dart` → `Insight.screen('offline');` in build/init;
  emit `Insight.event('offline_retry');` in the Retry handler.
- `lib/screens/menu_screen.dart` → `Insight.screen('menu');`
- `lib/screens/levels_screen.dart` → `Insight.screen('levels');`
- `lib/screens/game_screen.dart` → `Insight.screen('game');` +
  `Insight.tag('level', '$level');` and `web`-independent win/lose events.

If a screen is a `StatelessWidget`, convert it to `StatefulWidget` and call
`Insight.screen(...)` in `initState` (do not spam it from `build`).

---

## 6. The funnel you get in the dashboard

```
route_web → web_open → web_offer_reached ─┐ (or web_offer_unreachable + reason)
                                          ├→ web_register_page/click → web_register_submit
                                          ├→ web_login_page/click    → web_login_submit
                                          └→ web_cashier_page        → web_deposit_click
```

Slice by tags: `aid`, `run_mode`, `last_screen`, `notif_permission`,
`offer_reached`, `web_error_reason`, `reached_register/login/cashier`.

## 7. Hard rules

- ❌ Never call the Clarity SDK directly — always go through `Insight`
  (guarded). A Clarity failure must never break the gray flow.
- ❌ Never reuse a Clarity `projectId` across projects (`[FINGERPRINT]`).
- ✅ Keep event names STABLE and few. Put high-cardinality values
  (urls, hosts, labels, error text) in TAGS, not event names.
- ✅ `identify()` only after `af_id` is known (post `assembleGateBody`).
- ✅ The JS probe must stay idempotent (`window.__aegisInsight` guard).
